{"change_summary":"Made milestone task-run records conform to the current schema instead of carrying migration scaffolding. `TaskRunEntry.milestone_id` is now a required `String`, filesystem reads/writes no longer backfill or patch missing milestone IDs, legacy comma-delimited completion-journal parsing was removed so journal repair only accepts the structured JSON format, and start-attempt matching now uses `started_at` to distinguish same-attempt replays from genuinely new retries. I also removed obsolete backward-compat tests, required `skipped_beads` during progress deserialization, and added regressions covering runless retry splitting and same-attempt run-id backfill.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Attempts that still omit `run_id` remain ambiguous for completion updates when multiple same-project runless attempts are open at once; this round preserves that audit history instead of collapsing it, but deterministic finalization still depends on richer caller metadata."],"steps":[{"description":"Updated the milestone model to require explicit `milestone_id`, removed `skipped_beads` deserialization fallback, and tightened running-attempt matching so only same-attempt replays reuse an existing open row.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Simplified the filesystem adapters by deleting migration-only task-run backfill and legacy completion-detail parsing, and by validating that appended task-run rows already carry the correct milestone ID.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Reworked milestone-record tests to drop obsolete backward-compat coverage and add retry-vs-replay regressions for runless retries and newly named replays.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Reformatted and revalidated the milestone-record path plus bead hygiene checks after the changes.","order":3,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 99 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully.","`br lint` passed with no template warnings (`77 issues checked`)."]}